{"scriptures":{"scriptures":[{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":1,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018001,"content":"And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> appeared to him by the <crossref let=\"o\" cid=\"c01018001.1\"/>oaks<footnote>Or <i>terebinths</i></footnote> of Mamre, as he sat at the door of his tent in the heat of the day.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":2,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018002,"content":"He lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, three men were standing in front of him. <crossref let=\"p\" cid=\"c01018002.1\"/>When he saw them, he ran from the tent door to meet them and bowed himself to the earth","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":3,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018003,"content":"and said, \"O Lord,<footnote>Or <i>My lord</i></footnote> if I have found favor in your sight, do not pass by your servant.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":4,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018004,"content":"Let a <crossref let=\"q\" cid=\"c01018004.1\"/>little water be brought, and wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":5,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018005,"content":"while I bring a morsel of bread, that <crossref let=\"r\" cid=\"c01018005.1\"/>you may refresh yourselves, and after that you may pass on - <crossref let=\"s\" cid=\"c01018005.2\"/>since you have come to your servant. \" So they said, \"Do as you have said. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":6,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018006,"content":"And Abraham went quickly into the tent to Sarah and said, \"Quick! Three seahs<footnote>A <i class=\"catch-word-plural\">seah</i> was about 7 quarts or 7. 3 liters</footnote> of fine flour! Knead it, and make cakes. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":7,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018007,"content":"And Abraham ran to the herd and took a calf, tender and good, and gave it to a young man, who prepared it quickly.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":108,"verse":8,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018008,"content":"Then he took curds and milk and the calf that he had prepared, and set it before them. And he stood by them under the tree while they ate.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":9,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018009,"content":"They said to him, \"Where is Sarah your wife?\" And he said, \"She is <crossref let=\"t\" cid=\"c01018009.1\"/>in the tent. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":10,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018010,"content":"The <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said, \"I will surely return to you <crossref let=\"u\" cid=\"c01018010.1\"/>about this time next year, and <crossref let=\"v\" cid=\"c01018010.2\"/>Sarah your wife shall have a son. \" And Sarah was listening at the tent door behind him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":11,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018011,"content":"Now <crossref let=\"w\" cid=\"c01018011.1\"/>Abraham and Sarah were old, advanced in years. The way of women had ceased to be with Sarah.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":12,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018012,"content":"<crossref let=\"x\" cid=\"c01018012.1\"/>So Sarah laughed to herself, saying, <crossref let=\"y\" cid=\"c01018012.2\"/>\"After I am worn out, and <crossref let=\"z\" cid=\"c01018012.3\"/>my lord is old, shall I have pleasure?\"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":13,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018013,"content":"The <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said to Abraham, \"Why did Sarah laugh and say, 'Shall I indeed bear a child, now that I am old?'","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":14,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018014,"content":"<crossref let=\"a\" cid=\"c01018014.1\"/>Is anything too hard<footnote>Or <i>wonderful</i></footnote> for the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>? <crossref let=\"b\" cid=\"c01018014.2\"/>At the appointed time I will return to you, about this time next year, and Sarah shall have a son. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":109,"verse":15,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018015,"content":"But Sarah denied it,<footnote>Or <i>acted falsely</i></footnote> saying, \"I did not laugh,\" for she was afraid. He said, \"No, but you did laugh. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":16,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018016,"content":"Then the men set out from there, and they looked down toward Sodom. And Abraham went with them to set them on their way.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":17,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018017,"content":"The <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said, <crossref let=\"c\" cid=\"c01018017.1\"/>\"Shall I hide from Abraham what I am about to do,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":18,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018018,"content":"seeing that Abraham shall surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth shall be <crossref let=\"d\" cid=\"c01018018.1\"/>blessed in him?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":19,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018019,"content":"For I have <crossref let=\"e\" cid=\"c01018019.1\"/>chosen<footnote>Hebrew <i>known</i></footnote> him, that he may command his children and his household after him to keep the way of the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> by doing righteousness and justice, so that the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> may bring to Abraham what he has promised him. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":20,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018020,"content":"Then the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said, \"Because <crossref let=\"f\" cid=\"c01018020.1\"/>the outcry against Sodom and Gomorrah is great and their sin is very grave,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":110,"verse":21,"section_id":24,"block":null,"verse_id":1018021,"content":"<crossref let=\"g\" cid=\"c01018021.1\"/>I will go down to see whether they have done altogether<footnote>Or <i><span class=\"catch-word\">they</span> deserve destruction</i>; Hebrew <i><span class=\"catch-word\">they</span> have made a complete end</i></footnote> according to the outcry that has come to me. And if not, <crossref let=\"h\" cid=\"c01018021.2\"/>I will know. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Isaac's Birth Promised"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":111,"verse":22,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018022,"content":"<crossref let=\"i\" cid=\"c01018022.1\"/>So the men turned from there and went toward Sodom, but Abraham <crossref let=\"j\" cid=\"c01018022.2\"/>still stood before the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span>.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":111,"verse":23,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018023,"content":"Then Abraham drew near and said, <crossref let=\"k\" cid=\"c01018023.1\"/>\"Will you indeed sweep away the righteous with the wicked?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":111,"verse":24,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018024,"content":"Suppose there are fifty righteous within the city. Will you then sweep away the place and not spare it for the fifty righteous who are in it?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":111,"verse":25,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018025,"content":"Far be it from you to do such a thing, to put the righteous to death with the wicked, <crossref let=\"l\" cid=\"c01018025.1\"/>so that the righteous fare as the wicked! Far be that from you! <crossref let=\"m\" cid=\"c01018025.2\"/>Shall not the Judge of all the earth do what is just?\"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":111,"verse":26,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018026,"content":"And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> said, <crossref let=\"n\" cid=\"c01018026.1\"/>\"If I find at Sodom fifty righteous in the city, I will spare the whole place for their sake. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":27,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018027,"content":"Abraham answered and said, <crossref let=\"o\" cid=\"c01018027.1\"/>\"Behold, I have undertaken to speak to the Lord, I who am but dust and ashes.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":28,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018028,"content":"Suppose five of the fifty righteous are lacking. Will you destroy the whole city for lack of five?\" And he said, \"I will not destroy it if I find forty-five there. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":29,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018029,"content":"Again he spoke to him and said, \"Suppose forty are found there. \" He answered, \"For the sake of forty I will not do it. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":30,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018030,"content":"Then he said, \"Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak. Suppose thirty are found there. \" He answered, \"I will not do it, if I find thirty there. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":31,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018031,"content":"He said, \"Behold, I have undertaken to speak to the Lord. Suppose twenty are found there. \" He answered, \"For the sake of twenty I will not destroy it. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":32,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018032,"content":"Then he said, <crossref let=\"p\" cid=\"c01018032.1\"/>\"Oh let not the Lord be angry, and I will speak again but this once. Suppose ten are found there. \" He answered, \"For the sake of ten I will not destroy it. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"},{"chapter":18,"paragraph":112,"verse":33,"section_id":25,"block":null,"verse_id":1018033,"content":"And the <span class=\"divine-name\">Lord</span> went his way, when he had finished speaking to Abraham, and Abraham returned to his place. <end-chapter/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Abraham Intercedes for Sodom"}],"x_refs":{"c01018009.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"24:67","start_ref_id":1024067,"verse_id":1018009,"letter_id":"t"}],"c01018012.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Luke 1:18","start_ref_id":42001018,"verse_id":1018012,"letter_id":"y"}],"c01018021.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"11:5","start_ref_id":1011005,"verse_id":1018021,"letter_id":"g"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_tit